
[1]propitiatory

   PROPI'TIATORY, a. Having the power to make propitious; as a
   propitiatory sacrifice.

   PROPI'TIATORY, n. Among the Jews,the mercy-seat; the lid or cover of
   the ark of the covenant, lined within and without with plates of gold.
   This was a type of Christ.
